
Install Requirements:

- GCC 4.5.0 - not yet released, use a snapshot. You really need this as it features lambdas and more.
- LUA 5.1.3
- boost 1.41
- cmake 2.8.0 - for building
- cppunit 1.12.1 - for unit tests
- Asio - standalone version (ideally via CVS tag: linux-perf-branch)

fetch the sources from github.com/trapni/x0 (i guess you already did that).

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
HOW TO BUILD:

# we first need a special Asio tree:
cvs -d:pserver:anonymous@asio.cvs.sourceforge.net:/cvsroot/asio login 
cvs -z3 -d:pserver:anonymous@asio.cvs.sourceforge.net:/cvsroot/asio co -P asio
cd asio/
cvs co -r linux-perf-branch .
cd ../

# now lets fetch and compile x0
git clone git://github.com/trapni/x0.git
cd x0/
cmake . -DASIO_INCLUDEDIR=$(dirname $(pwd))/asio
make
cd src/
./x0d --no-fork --config=test.conf         # or in short: ./x0d -X -c test.conf

# have fun hacking.
